Definition of Idea Man
There are two definitions of [idea man].
　People who come up with [ideas] that no one else has come up with.
　People who have a high probability of coming up with good ideas.

People who have a high probability of coming up with good ideas have a high probability of saying something that is not new.
　Most problems are derivatives of problems solved in the past
　I'll say the obvious again and again.
　　I'll say it again and again if it's a good idea.
　　[Novelty is not important.

People who come up with ideas that no one else has thought of are new.
　There's no guarantee it's a useful idea.
　Because no one has yet validated [the usefulness] of anything new.
